    "Body": " Senior IT Auditor Texas Municipal Retirement System - 4.5 Austin, TX Apply Now Job Details Full-timeEstimated: $85,000 - $120,000 a year Qualifications CPA Certified Internal Auditor Network Security CISSP Certified Information Systems Auditor Full Job Description Level Experienced Job Location Austin - Austin, TX Senior IT Auditor Texas Municipal Retirement System (TMRS), a $30 billion pension plan located in Austin, Texas, is seeking to hire an Information Technology Senior Auditor. Providing secure, reliable retirement benefits to nearly 175,000 members through our unique hybrid defined benefit / defined contribution structure, TMRS seeks to be the model for empowering retirement. The Internal Audit Department reports to the TMRS Board of Trustees through the Internal Audit Committee. The position will interact with senior management throughout the organization and will report to the Internal Audit Director. The position will be responsible for performing internal audit advisory, assurance, and consulting services, with emphasis on information technology topics. This is a senior level position that performs moderately complex activities generally specializing in the functional area of Internal Audit IT and with the ability to contribute across functional areas of Audit. Activities include in depth exposure to IT systems and technical professionals working in software development, change management, access control, IT infrastructure, information and network security, server virtualization, cloud computing, mobile applications, and other key areas of our company. The IT Auditor should demonstrate behavior that meets professional auditing standards for confidentiality, integrity, and ethics; and the Auditor will work under limited supervision, with considerable latitude for the use of initiative and independent judgment. The position will be filled at a level commensurate with experience. Responsibilities: Developing and maintaining the IT Risk Assessment including identifying areas where internal audit should focus. Conducting audits and reviews of IT functions, IT processes, and IT systems against regulations, standards, and industry practices such as COBIT, ISO, NIST, and ITIL. Performing IT security audits (e.g. network, operating system and data center), including evaluating if security vulnerabilities are properly identified and mitigated. Reviewing and recommending information technology controls to mitigate information technology risks regarding the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of business information. Verifying compliance with laws, regulations, and policies on privacy and public access to data, and testing controls over online services. Performing reviews of IT management policies and procedures such as change management, business continuity planning / disaster recovery, and information security to ensure that controls surrounding these processes are adequate. Participating in reviews of internal controls and security of systems under development as well as major IT projects and initiatives. Preparing and reviewing audit reports dealing with complex and sensitive issues in a timely manner, and reporting results to executives and the Internal Audit Committee. Evaluating data extraction, analysis, and security reviews, including SOC reports. Providing technical support for audits, and developing, building, and implementing tools to analyze data to improve audit efficiency and effectiveness, provide business insights, or for continuous auditing. May serve as a subject matter expert on IT risk management matters, particularly on application and infrastructure security. Minimum Qualifications Graduation from an accredited four (4) year college or university. Four years of experience in information system audit techniques, network security, technology infrastructure, software development, or a related field. Demonstrated research and analysis capabilities. Demonstrated oral and written communication capabilities. Substitutions for Experience The following can substitute for up to two (2) years of required experience. Relevant advanced degree can substitute for one (1) year of experience. Pension or investment experience can substitute for one (1) year of experience. IT or security certification, such as CISA or CISSP, can substitute for one (1) year of experience. Preferred Qualifications Major course work in information systems, computer science, IT risk management/governance, accounting, business administration, finance, economics, public affairs/administration, or a related field is generally preferred. Technical understanding in several of the following areas: Networks Operating Systems (Windows, Unix, Linux) Databases (Oracle, SQL Server) PC, thin clients, and mobile devices Routers, firewalls, log aggregators, and IPS/IDS Web technologies Cloud technologies IT development and operations, including JAVA Telecommunications Certification as a Certified Information Systems Auditor (CISA), Certified Information Systems Security Professional (CISSP), Certified Security Professional, Certified Public Accountant (CPA), Certified Internal Auditor (CIA), or other certification for which internal audit has a need. Pension and investment experience. Proficient in Excel, IDEA, ACL or similar applications. "
